[2] UK: Ebola advice for dental care teams
Date: Mon 22 Dec 2014
Source: UK government, Public Health England report [edited]
https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ebola-advice-for-dental-care-teams


UK: Ebola advice for dental care teams
--------------------------------------
The UK has published guidance for dental practice staff who encounter patients with Ebola virus disease (EVD): PHE [Public Health England] publications gateway number: 2014616 (PDF). The document contains information on: transmission, symptoms, identifying patients at risk, dental care, general standards of infection control and decontamination [of EVD]. The basic message is that it is important for the protection of patients, public and dental teams that high standards of infection control and decontamination are in place at all times, even though risk of infection in the UK is considered low.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Precautions dental care team workers must take to prevent infection are similar to those for any caretaker handling potentially infected individuals. - Mod.LK]

