******
[4] USA (Georgia): CDC worker monitored for possible Ebola exposure
Date: Thu 25 Dec 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/12/25/us-health-ebola-usa-idUSKBN0K21BQ20141225


CDC laboratory worker monitored for possible Ebola exposure
-----------------------------------------------------------
A laboratory technician for the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention [CDC] has been placed under observation for possible exposure to Ebola virus due to an apparent mix-up in lab specimens, the Atlanta [Georgia]-based agency said on Wednesday [24 Dec 2014]. The technician, who was working on Monday [22 Dec 2014] with Ebola specimens that were supposed to have been inactivated but which may instead have contained live virus, will be monitored for signs of infection for 21 days, the disease's incubation period, CDC officials said...

[byline: Steve Gorman]

